nership and possession that arose from these disputes. Tate argues that the innovations made necessary by advowson law helped give birth to modern common law and common law courts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2022) 0aAdvowson. 0aPatronage, EcclesiasticalzEngland. 0aPossession (Law)zEnglandxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Norman Conquest to Late Medieval (1066-1485).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074977940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030016471840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300164718423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300164718/original  a978-3-11-074977-9  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles